Rating: 3
This is my second review of this recipe. I've made it about 5-6 times and have to say that it hasn't always been consistent. My findings? A glass (I use Pyrex) or metal pan is essential. Making sure the butter and pan are REALLY hot is also important. Oddly enough, I found salted butter worked better than unsalted. While the butter is heating in the oven, I bread the chicken and set aside so its ready to go when the pan comes out. Also, SEASON that flour! Its like mashed potatoes... You have to put in alot of seasoning because its such a bland ingredient. I put cayenne, paprika, garlic salt and lots of cracked black pepper. If the skin side of the chicken doesn't crisp up as well as you like it, put it under the broiler for a few minutes. Also, when removing the chicken to make a gravy, put the chicken on a wire rack in a warm place. I found stacking the chicken created steam and soggy skin! Hope all this research assists you make this recipe. I like it a great deal.

