Having had the benefit of reading other reviewers' comments and suggestions for this recipe, I think I found the combination that worked for me. Used buttermilk. Not a user of seasoned salt, I increased the plain salt to 2 1/2 tsp., and added 1/4 tsp. each of crumbled, dried sage and thyme. Reduced the fat to 2 Tbsp. each butter and canola oil. Simplified the gravy by adding the seasoned flour (which I'd removed before shaking the chicken) to the pan drippings, and using chicken broth as the liquid. The chicken came crispy, not greasy, and both chicken and gravy were flavorful.

