This is good old-fashioned comfort food- a dinner that Grandma would have served at Sunday supper. I used a boxed seasoned flour mix and skipped the scallions and mushrooms. I used Vidalia onions for the gravy instead. I used only 4 tablespoons of margarine and still felt it was a bit greasy but I guess it was necessary to produce a nice crispy skin.

